Two years ago, the South African government launched the Pre-exposure prophylaxis or PrEP, which provides protection to those who are at substantial risk of HIV infection from their sexual partners.Â 

However, the uptake of PrEP has been very low in South Africa. Scientists are now looking at innovative ways of administering the drug which has been proved to provide significant protection against HIV infection.

